This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) because it presents a new framework for compositional distributional semantics that involves analyzing the distributional contexts of lexemes. It is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories because it proposes a method for capturing and generalizing distributional knowledge. Additionally, it may belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories because the proposed framework could potentially be applied to these areas.
